WEBVTT

00:12.621 --> 00:14.666
♪

00:30.030 --> 00:32.032
♪

00:38.125 --> 00:41.084
HE--
Hear me, OÓdinn,

00:41.128 --> 00:42.955
All-Father of the gods.

00:44.348 --> 00:47.090
Summon the shadows of ages past,

00:47.134 --> 00:52.617
when the thread spinning Norns
ruled the fates of men.

00:53.662 --> 00:56.360
Hear of
a prince's vengeance quenched

00:56.404 --> 00:59.755
at the fiery Gates of Hel.

00:59.798 --> 01:03.063
A prince destined for Valhoöll.

01:04.238 --> 01:06.109
Hear me.

01:10.113 --> 01:12.115
♪

01:22.343 --> 01:24.388
♪

01:47.237 --> 01:49.283
♪

01:54.157 --> 01:55.767
He's here.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.122
He's here.

02:03.166 --> 02:06.648
-Mother, Father is here!

02:08.215 --> 02:10.913
Never enter my chambers
without invitation!

02:10.956 --> 02:13.220
The king, milady. The king.

02:18.442 --> 02:19.878
GUDRUÚ-
Come.

02:19.922 --> 02:21.619
OÓdinn brought him home.

02:29.192 --> 02:31.194
♪

02:44.686 --> 02:46.601
Hail, Raven King!

02:50.387 --> 02:52.433
War-Raven, hail!

02:55.000 --> 02:56.654
Hail, my lord!

03:00.180 --> 03:01.485
War-Raven, hail.

03:02.486 --> 03:04.140
Hail, ring giver!

03:10.712 --> 03:12.757
♪

03:24.291 --> 03:25.857
FJOÖ-
Onward, brother!

03:35.824 --> 03:37.129
Come here.

03:39.915 --> 03:41.960
-Go.

03:44.093 --> 03:46.138
♪

03:55.626 --> 03:59.195
CROWD
Hail, King Aurvandil War-Raven!

03:59.239 --> 04:00.718
Hail!

04:06.855 --> 04:09.727
Like a battle-dog
returning to its master,

04:09.771 --> 04:13.992
I've come to be fettered
by my queen's fair locks.

04:14.036 --> 04:16.517
Ever are we bound, my lord.

04:19.302 --> 04:21.826
Prince Amleth,

04:21.870 --> 04:25.743
you have grown too old
to be greeted as a child.

04:30.574 --> 04:32.620
Hail, Lord King.

04:34.578 --> 04:36.493
But...

04:36.537 --> 04:39.453
a father never grows too old

04:39.496 --> 04:41.498
-for a good smothering!

04:41.542 --> 04:43.979
How I've missed you, my son.

04:47.330 --> 04:50.333
Will your brother not
grace us with his presence?

04:50.377 --> 04:52.727
Think not on Fjoölnir.

04:52.770 --> 04:54.468
He'll soon be with us.

04:55.425 --> 04:57.471
♪

05:21.364 --> 05:26.804
This was worn round a
prince's neck when I found it.

05:26.848 --> 05:30.982
But it was destined
for this prince.

05:31.026 --> 05:33.507
Wear it always with my love.

05:33.550 --> 05:35.509
Thank you, Father.

05:35.552 --> 05:37.032
My king.

05:39.513 --> 05:41.297
Fjoölnir.

05:41.341 --> 05:42.690
-MAN Fjoölnir's back.

05:42.733 --> 05:44.387
-The brute has arrived.

05:44.909 --> 05:47.651
The brute has arrived.

05:57.226 --> 05:58.967
Hail, Lord King.

06:01.578 --> 06:05.234
Furnish this fierce-hearted
slayer of men with some drink,

06:05.277 --> 06:07.671
that I might drink to him.

06:07.715 --> 06:11.893
Accept my cup, kinsman.

06:11.936 --> 06:13.982
-Milady.

06:15.113 --> 06:20.684
Look how the queen's cup grows
wet for more men than her king.

06:20.728 --> 06:23.426
What metal might buy
a fragrant sip?

06:23.470 --> 06:25.602
Sweet silver...

06:25.646 --> 06:27.996
or hard iron?

06:28.039 --> 06:30.564
Silence, dog!

06:30.607 --> 06:33.958
By Freyr, you slander
your lord and mistress!

06:34.002 --> 06:35.917
-Please you, brother.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.440
'Tis but a jest.

06:37.484 --> 06:38.876
A jest.

06:38.920 --> 06:40.617
Heimir keeps a foul tongue,

06:40.661 --> 06:43.794
yet I keep him
as a deep-sworn friend.

06:45.274 --> 06:47.407
Come, brother.

06:47.450 --> 06:51.193
Here's one more in need of
your safekeeping than myself.

06:52.760 --> 06:54.283
FJOÖLNIR
Thórir.

06:58.243 --> 06:59.810
Thórir!

06:59.854 --> 07:02.334
My son!

07:02.378 --> 07:05.381
To my brother, the War-Raven!

07:05.425 --> 07:07.078
To the Kingdom of Hrafnsey!

07:07.122 --> 07:09.472
Skál!

07:26.663 --> 07:29.449
- The enemy
had a taste of my liver.

07:32.582 --> 07:34.149
Are you hurt?

07:34.192 --> 07:38.545
Almost enough for Amleth
to be marked my successor.

07:39.981 --> 07:42.374
I watched his innocence tonight.

07:43.767 --> 07:46.248
He must be awoken
to what awaits him.

07:47.554 --> 07:48.946
He is a puppy.

07:48.990 --> 07:50.861
He's the same age
as my grandfather

07:50.905 --> 07:52.341
when he took the throne.

07:52.384 --> 07:54.735
That was different.

07:54.778 --> 07:57.346
He had to kill his uncle first.

08:01.002 --> 08:04.092
You have not seen your queen
in a season.

08:04.135 --> 08:05.441
Come.

08:06.573 --> 08:08.966
Let me take you to our bed.

08:17.714 --> 08:19.716
No.

08:19.760 --> 08:23.111
Pray my luck-spirits
see me to many war fields

08:23.154 --> 08:25.069
after I defeat this wound.

08:25.113 --> 08:27.507
I refuse to die in sickness

08:27.550 --> 08:31.598
nor live the long life
of a shameful graybeard.

08:31.641 --> 08:34.992
I must die by the sword.

08:35.036 --> 08:38.735
I will die in honor.

08:41.042 --> 08:42.739
Fret not.

08:45.263 --> 08:48.789
You will die
in battle, my lord.

08:50.138 --> 08:53.054
The Gates of Valhoöll
await you, I know it.

09:02.542 --> 09:06.546
- This is the same
path I walked with my father

09:06.589 --> 09:08.504
and he with his.

09:09.636 --> 09:13.204
Now it is our path to walk.

09:13.248 --> 09:15.380
♪

09:57.640 --> 09:59.163
AMLETH
OÓdinn.

10:24.232 --> 10:26.277
♪

10:41.031 --> 10:43.425
Be not afraid, Amleth.

10:43.468 --> 10:45.296
Do as I do.

11:06.274 --> 11:07.362
Who barks?

11:08.798 --> 11:11.714
Is it the wolves
of the High One?

11:14.108 --> 11:17.894
Or is it the barking
of the village dogs?

11:19.156 --> 11:23.160
Harken to me,
you two-legged dogs.

11:23.204 --> 11:26.860
Drink the vision mead
of knowledge.

11:26.903 --> 11:31.038
To learn what it is
to live and die in honor.

11:31.081 --> 11:33.431
-To be in battle slain

11:33.475 --> 11:37.958
and in death rewarded by
the Valkyrjur's embrace.

11:38.001 --> 11:39.829
The warrior maidens
will carry you

11:39.873 --> 11:42.876
to the shimmering
Gates of Valhoöll.

11:46.227 --> 11:49.230
You are dogs
that wish to become men.

11:52.233 --> 11:55.018
Prove you are not a dog.

12:00.807 --> 12:04.375
Not only are you a man,
you dine like a king.

12:14.864 --> 12:18.346
And you, little cub,
what are you?

12:21.436 --> 12:23.090
-Ah.

12:23.133 --> 12:25.701
I smell a clever pupil.

12:28.748 --> 12:30.967
At every passage,

12:31.011 --> 12:33.143
one should turn his eye round,

12:33.187 --> 12:35.058
one should spy round.

12:35.102 --> 12:38.496
For a foe might be
crouched within upon the floor.

12:38.540 --> 12:41.761
Wise in measure
should each man be,

12:41.804 --> 12:43.458
yet wise enough to be the fool.

12:43.501 --> 12:45.547
Wise enough to be the fool.

12:45.590 --> 12:50.117
Tell me,
how did OÓdinn lose his eye?

12:50.160 --> 12:51.814
To learn
the secret magic of women.

12:51.858 --> 12:55.949
Never seek the secrets of
women, but heed them always.

12:55.992 --> 12:59.474
- It is women that know
the mysteries of men.

12:59.517 --> 13:04.305
The Norns that spin and weave
at their Well of Fate.

13:04.348 --> 13:07.482
-Live in honor.
-Live in honor.

13:07.525 --> 13:11.138
-Safeguard your familial blood.
-Safeguard your familial blood.

13:11.181 --> 13:13.618
Know you what that means,
Amleth, son of Aurvandil?

13:15.011 --> 13:17.840
Should I fall
by the enemy's sword,

13:17.884 --> 13:22.236
you must avenge me
or forever live in shame!

13:22.279 --> 13:24.151
I will, Father, I will!

13:24.194 --> 13:25.674
My blade will not rest

13:25.717 --> 13:27.328
till it's drunk the blood
from his open neck!

13:27.371 --> 13:30.548
Now live always without fear,

13:30.592 --> 13:33.856
for your fate is set
and you cannot scape it.

13:33.900 --> 13:35.727
Swear it.

13:35.771 --> 13:37.512
I swear.

13:40.776 --> 13:42.822
♪

13:58.402 --> 14:00.448
♪

14:20.163 --> 14:24.602
This is the last tear
you will shed in weakness.

14:24.646 --> 14:28.302
It will be given back
when most you need it.

14:29.738 --> 14:33.176
Now, behold,

14:33.220 --> 14:34.874
as a man.

14:41.881 --> 14:44.274
Approach, Amleth,

14:44.318 --> 14:50.280
and in our blood
behold the tree of kings.

15:11.475 --> 15:13.521
♪

15:23.923 --> 15:25.925
♪

16:35.995 --> 16:37.213
Father!

16:38.606 --> 16:41.130
Run! Run!

16:48.529 --> 16:52.054
Come for your carcass,
you mongrels!

17:16.774 --> 17:18.820
♪

17:46.369 --> 17:49.372
You behold your brother's gaze
in amazement.

17:51.679 --> 17:53.681
I knew well you would.

17:55.813 --> 17:59.730
Pity you never paid
a bastard's eyes heed before.

18:02.385 --> 18:07.738
Now... behold how swiftly
your brother swings his sword.

18:11.002 --> 18:15.268
Strike, brother, strike.

18:16.356 --> 18:18.836
But know
that bearing a stolen ring

18:18.880 --> 18:21.143
makes no half-breed a king.

18:21.187 --> 18:23.667
Soaked in my blood,

18:23.711 --> 18:29.151
it will soon be sliding
off your arm like a serpent.

18:29.195 --> 18:34.156
Your kingdom will not last.

18:39.466 --> 18:44.210
Let this misdeed
haunt your living nights

18:44.253 --> 18:48.344
till a flaming vengeance
gorges on your death.

18:50.912 --> 18:52.261
Strike.

18:54.350 --> 18:55.612
Strike!

18:56.613 --> 18:58.398
To Valhoöll!

19:10.888 --> 19:13.630
King Aurvandil is dead!

19:15.066 --> 19:18.461
-Long live King Fjoölnir!
-Long live King Fjoölnir!

19:18.505 --> 19:20.550
MEN
Hail, Lord King!

19:20.594 --> 19:22.639
Hail, Lord King!

19:27.209 --> 19:28.819
Bring me the boy's head!

19:30.560 --> 19:32.606
♪

19:45.445 --> 19:47.838
-Do you see him?

19:47.882 --> 19:49.840
-Over here.
-Cut him off!

19:49.884 --> 19:51.929
♪

20:11.949 --> 20:13.516
I'll make it slow.

20:29.706 --> 20:31.752
♪

20:51.032 --> 20:53.904
Hail, Fjoölnir the Brotherless!

20:53.948 --> 20:55.819
Hail, King Fjoölnir!

20:55.863 --> 20:57.821
-Hail, Fjoölnir!

21:01.390 --> 21:03.436
Hail, King Fjoölnir!

21:04.480 --> 21:07.657
HALLGRIÍ- King Fjoölnir
has found himself a queen.

21:11.182 --> 21:12.532
Fjoölnir!

21:12.575 --> 21:15.274
Fjoölnir! My lord!

21:15.317 --> 21:16.405
The boy!

21:17.363 --> 21:19.016
The boy.

21:20.757 --> 21:23.586
The boy is dead.

21:23.630 --> 21:26.110
Dead in the sea.

21:26.154 --> 21:27.721
Yeah.

21:27.764 --> 21:29.679
Sank like a stone.

21:34.771 --> 21:36.817
♪

21:38.601 --> 21:40.037
I will avenge you, Father!

21:40.081 --> 21:41.778
I will save you, Mother!

21:41.822 --> 21:43.693
I will kill you, Fjoölnir!

21:43.737 --> 21:45.608
I will avenge you, Father!

21:45.652 --> 21:47.218
I will save you, Mother!

21:47.262 --> 21:49.090
I will kill you, Fjoölnir!

21:49.133 --> 21:50.874
I will avenge you, Father!

21:50.918 --> 21:52.833
I will save you, Mother!

21:52.876 --> 21:54.878
I will kill you, Fjoölnir!

21:54.922 --> 21:56.576
I will avenge you, Father!

21:56.619 --> 21:58.404
I will save you, Mother!

21:58.447 --> 22:00.493
I will kill you, Fjoölnir!

22:17.423 --> 22:19.425
♪

22:53.154 --> 22:55.199
♪

23:15.176 --> 23:17.221
♪

26:08.218 --> 26:10.177
To Valhoöll!

26:10.220 --> 26:12.266
♪

27:36.002 --> 27:37.656
No!

28:23.919 --> 28:25.399
What are you doing?

28:25.442 --> 28:26.922
Come now, come. Come here.

28:26.966 --> 28:28.271
Come here.

28:46.507 --> 28:50.641
These savages
make for fine chattel,

28:50.685 --> 28:52.208
eh, Bjoörnulfr?

28:52.252 --> 28:54.471
We did good.

28:54.515 --> 28:56.082
Never better.

28:59.868 --> 29:01.914
When we found you as a cub...

29:03.654 --> 29:07.397
...I knew then that you had
a heart of cold iron.

29:07.441 --> 29:09.617
-- Too weak!

29:09.660 --> 29:11.445
I want strong ones!

29:11.488 --> 29:13.534
Not weak ones!

29:13.577 --> 29:15.623
♪

29:24.327 --> 29:25.720
Mama!

29:28.679 --> 29:30.029
Mama!

29:32.031 --> 29:33.249
Mama!

29:37.819 --> 29:39.168
Mama!

29:47.873 --> 29:49.352
Mama!

29:51.615 --> 29:53.356
Mama!

29:55.228 --> 29:57.012
Mama!

30:34.267 --> 30:36.356
Play, you idiot. Play!

30:55.070 --> 30:57.116
♪

31:17.658 --> 31:19.703
♪

32:07.708 --> 32:09.666
♪

32:23.289 --> 32:27.989
Prowl in shadow,
slayer of my people.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.338
Hide.

32:31.862 --> 32:34.865
Even though your brother
stole my eyes...

32:36.432 --> 32:38.086
...I see you.

32:39.261 --> 32:41.742
I am no one's brother.

32:42.786 --> 32:47.226
It is not enough
to be the man that never cries,

32:47.269 --> 32:49.793
Prince Amleth.

32:51.447 --> 32:55.364
The prince that turned
from his fate.

32:56.452 --> 33:00.239
A beast that cares for naught.

33:00.282 --> 33:03.851
A beast that wrings tears
from the eyes of men.

33:06.332 --> 33:12.251
Now remember for whom
you shed your last teardrop.

33:12.294 --> 33:15.123
Remember the oath
to right the wrong.

33:16.298 --> 33:19.171
Remember the Raven King.

33:19.214 --> 33:21.347
Remember.

33:21.390 --> 33:26.047
Remember,
it contains the salty ocean

33:26.091 --> 33:29.877
you must sail upon
to the edge of the world.

33:29.920 --> 33:34.273
It feeds the freezing river
of hate that runs in my veins.

33:34.316 --> 33:38.538
It will take you
to an island in the north

33:38.581 --> 33:41.932
where there will spring
a burning lake,

33:41.976 --> 33:45.458
bursting from
a black mountain's peak.

33:45.501 --> 33:49.723
There I will drown
my father's killer.

33:49.766 --> 33:54.554
Follow the vixen's tail to
the dwelling of the ancient one

33:54.597 --> 33:59.907
to seek the fated sword
that matches your brutal rage.

33:59.950 --> 34:04.085
Why speak you my fortune, witch?

34:04.129 --> 34:08.350
For where your path
of ashes ends,

34:08.394 --> 34:11.962
another will begin her journey.

34:13.007 --> 34:15.357
A maiden king.

34:15.401 --> 34:17.142
Release me.

34:17.185 --> 34:20.667
You cannot scape what fate
the Norns have spun.

34:21.668 --> 34:24.236
-Now begone!

34:27.978 --> 34:30.764
These slaves go to Uppsala.

34:33.723 --> 34:36.117
Those to the market in Kiev.

34:39.555 --> 34:42.254
Send them to Constantinople.

34:42.297 --> 34:45.735
And these strong ones
should make it all the way

34:45.779 --> 34:47.650
to Fjoölnir's post in Iceland.

34:50.262 --> 34:52.829
Who is this Fjoölnir?

34:52.873 --> 34:54.527
Fjoölnir the Brotherless.

34:54.570 --> 34:56.398
So-called after
he killed his brother,

34:56.442 --> 34:59.619
the disgraced
King Aurvandil War-Raven.

35:01.273 --> 35:03.405
I know of him.

35:03.449 --> 35:05.755
Why are his slaves
bound for Iceland?

35:05.799 --> 35:08.323
Fjoölnir rules over Hrafnsey.

35:08.367 --> 35:12.719
He fled to the backwater
frontier with his wife and son

35:12.762 --> 35:16.984
after King Haraldr of Norway
took his kingdom.

35:17.027 --> 35:19.029
Fjoölnir killed his brother
for nothing.

35:19.073 --> 35:20.596
Now he's a sheep farmer.

35:23.512 --> 35:26.341
♪

35:35.220 --> 35:36.656
Father.

35:59.766 --> 36:01.071
Worry not.

36:01.115 --> 36:02.508
When I meet your owner,

36:02.551 --> 36:04.945
I will thank him
for the warmth you gave me.

36:08.340 --> 36:10.559
♪

36:28.229 --> 36:29.796
Bring those two ropes.

36:32.015 --> 36:33.843
Take your place.

37:08.008 --> 37:10.053
♪

37:32.424 --> 37:34.164
Ah, how can he get that number?

37:34.208 --> 37:36.036
-- He's cheating.

37:36.079 --> 37:37.211
It is luck.

37:37.255 --> 37:39.169
Let's see what you've got.

37:39.213 --> 37:40.910
It continues then.

37:42.303 --> 37:44.262
I've lost all my silver, then.

37:50.398 --> 37:53.749
Your sheep's clothing does not
disguise you, Northman.

37:55.360 --> 37:58.232
What say you, spell speaker?

37:58.276 --> 38:01.191
You wish to be a slave,

38:01.235 --> 38:02.889
hide your cunning.

38:04.499 --> 38:07.197
Show the shepherd
you are a sheep.

38:07.241 --> 38:09.896
I'll show the shepherd
his death.

38:12.115 --> 38:13.769
♪

38:17.817 --> 38:19.732
Hold it strong!

38:23.388 --> 38:25.607
-- Stay on your feet!

38:27.392 --> 38:28.828
Take my hand!

38:30.438 --> 38:32.048
I have you!

38:52.547 --> 38:54.593
♪

39:05.734 --> 39:07.345
♪

39:21.446 --> 39:23.448
♪

39:33.849 --> 39:35.895
YOUNG AMLETH
I will avenge you, Father.

39:35.938 --> 39:37.984
I will save you, Mother.

39:38.027 --> 39:40.334
I will kill you, Fjoölnir.

39:59.135 --> 40:01.181
♪

40:13.411 --> 40:14.760
Over there.

40:19.765 --> 40:21.244
Leave her here.

40:22.202 --> 40:23.377
Move!

40:33.518 --> 40:36.434
-- Bunch of corpses.
-- Let him rot!

40:37.783 --> 40:40.046
The seagulls will eat him!

40:40.089 --> 40:41.917
They're hungry!

40:45.355 --> 40:47.793
Move, swine!

40:50.186 --> 40:52.232
♪

41:17.866 --> 41:21.087
Why would you stow away
to such a hellish place?

41:21.130 --> 41:23.959
This ground harbors evil.

41:24.003 --> 41:26.484
My fate has brought me here.

41:26.527 --> 41:29.356
To find what was stolen from me.

41:29.399 --> 41:30.879
And what is that?

41:31.967 --> 41:36.363
A mother, a father, a kingdom.

41:37.886 --> 41:39.671
This is your kingdom?

41:39.714 --> 41:41.629
The traitor who stole
my kingdom fled here

41:41.673 --> 41:43.718
when another king
took it from him.

41:45.024 --> 41:47.330
I will leave
when I'm done with him.

41:49.245 --> 41:52.118
I am Olga of the Birch Forest.

41:52.161 --> 41:55.687
And I, too,
vow to escape this island.

41:55.730 --> 41:58.516
Then you must face many foes.

41:58.559 --> 42:00.082
As do you.

42:02.041 --> 42:04.086
Would you face them alone?

42:06.436 --> 42:09.701
Your strength
breaks men's bones.

42:09.744 --> 42:11.964
I have the cunning
to break their minds.

42:12.007 --> 42:14.575
HALLGRIÍ-
You two, hold your traps!

42:14.619 --> 42:16.055
Walk on!

42:41.733 --> 42:43.473
Why are we doing this?

42:43.517 --> 42:44.910
What?

42:44.953 --> 42:46.955
-This.
-What?

42:46.999 --> 42:49.131
It's slave work.

42:49.175 --> 42:50.742
You're the chieftain.

42:50.785 --> 42:52.657
It's your temple,

42:52.700 --> 42:55.007
and I'm the heir
to this holy chiefdom.

42:55.050 --> 42:58.532
No man knows if he will
celebrate next yuletide

42:58.576 --> 43:01.491
as a king or as a slave.

43:01.535 --> 43:03.450
Best to be prepared for both.

43:03.493 --> 43:06.235
And to stave off the latter,
the least you can do

43:06.279 --> 43:09.369
is show your slaves
you're as strong as they are.

43:11.676 --> 43:14.592
But no one's watching us.

43:16.550 --> 43:18.117
Go fetch us some whey.

43:18.160 --> 43:19.814
Think on what I said.

43:19.858 --> 43:21.816
-- Keep your shield arm up.
-THOÓ- I am.

43:21.860 --> 43:23.165
-- You're...
-I am!

43:23.209 --> 43:24.427
You are not!

43:24.471 --> 43:25.994
-Attack, Hjalti!

43:28.823 --> 43:31.260
No! No!

43:35.047 --> 43:37.005
HALLGRIÍ-
Fjoölnir, my lord!

43:39.965 --> 43:42.402
Your shipment is here.

43:44.230 --> 43:47.015
Well, show me.

43:47.059 --> 43:49.452
-Where's the rest of them?
-HALLGRIÍ- Get on your feet!

43:49.496 --> 43:51.367
-- On your feet!
-On your feet!

43:51.411 --> 43:53.195
Up, swines!

43:53.239 --> 43:55.197
HALLGRIÍ-
Line up, bastards!

43:58.636 --> 44:01.639
THOÓ-
Pitiful. Can't even stand.

44:01.682 --> 44:03.684
♪

44:07.296 --> 44:09.342
FJOÖ-
They won't last the winter.

44:10.560 --> 44:12.388
Sell all of them.

44:23.835 --> 44:25.358
Let me see this one.

44:40.329 --> 44:42.723
We've kept worse.

44:54.604 --> 44:56.476
I'm not impressed.

44:58.304 --> 44:59.653
His stench.

45:03.875 --> 45:06.573
Never look me
in the eye, slave.

45:08.314 --> 45:11.578
Well, I wonder what they call
a beast like you

45:11.621 --> 45:13.711
in the Land of Rus.

45:16.757 --> 45:19.151
I am...

45:19.194 --> 45:22.067
Bjoörnulfr.

45:22.110 --> 45:25.287
By name alone, you can tell
he's as strong as a bear.

45:29.814 --> 45:32.207
But if you're
as untrustworthy as a wolf,

45:32.251 --> 45:34.949
I swear
I'll put you down myself.

45:39.214 --> 45:40.781
We keep this one.

45:42.087 --> 45:43.697
The rest can go.

45:46.308 --> 45:48.528
- But mother needs
two for the kitchen

45:48.571 --> 45:50.791
-and one for the laundry.
-- Move.

45:50.835 --> 45:52.184
And two males for the harvest.

45:52.227 --> 45:53.881
FJOÖ-
Fine.

45:53.925 --> 45:57.450
These two for the kitchen
and her for the laundry.

45:57.493 --> 46:00.235
And choose two males
for the fields.

46:02.107 --> 46:03.935
And her, too.

46:05.893 --> 46:07.765
Keep her arms white...

46:09.462 --> 46:11.812
...and her hair long.

46:11.856 --> 46:13.858
♪

46:32.441 --> 46:35.314
Plan to climb out, huh,
Bear-Wolf?

46:36.881 --> 46:39.753
Even if you did
escape this farm,

46:39.797 --> 46:43.626
you'd only be carrion
for the blue foxes and selkies.

46:44.932 --> 46:47.935
This island is a barren waste.

46:47.979 --> 46:50.329
You best find yourself
some sleep.

46:59.251 --> 47:01.296
♪

47:24.624 --> 47:26.669
♪

47:39.160 --> 47:41.554
VOÖ-
Get! Get!

47:41.597 --> 47:42.990
-Get!

47:44.078 --> 47:45.732
Thieving demon-bitch.

47:52.652 --> 47:54.697
♪

48:00.486 --> 48:02.705
GUDRUÚ-
Away! Away.

48:04.794 --> 48:07.058
Away with you!

48:08.929 --> 48:10.800
Away! Begone!

48:14.674 --> 48:16.110
Away with you!

48:18.330 --> 48:20.375
I will avenge you, Father.

48:22.116 --> 48:24.162
I will save you, Mother.

48:25.859 --> 48:27.817
I will kill you, Fjoölnir.

48:27.861 --> 48:29.907
♪

48:35.086 --> 48:36.783
-Here. Go.

49:05.812 --> 49:07.857
♪

49:16.301 --> 49:18.085
Go take a piss.

49:20.044 --> 49:21.175
HALLDOÓ-
In there.

49:35.842 --> 49:37.322
Stop there.

49:56.689 --> 49:58.560
You! Get on with it!

49:58.604 --> 50:00.084
On with you now!

50:15.229 --> 50:17.275
Where's your wits?

50:17.318 --> 50:18.798
Turn around.

50:31.332 --> 50:32.942
Shut the door.

50:50.264 --> 50:52.658
Did you find it?

50:52.701 --> 50:54.181
What you lost.

50:55.791 --> 50:57.837
In the house today,
was it there?

50:59.839 --> 51:01.971
That...

51:02.015 --> 51:03.495
and more.

51:11.111 --> 51:12.895
It's a nightmare.

51:15.594 --> 51:17.639
Then you must wake up.

51:19.076 --> 51:20.990
It's their nightmare.

51:22.601 --> 51:24.385
You!

51:24.429 --> 51:26.126
You, woman!

51:26.170 --> 51:27.780
You come with us!

51:28.781 --> 51:31.044
You don't belong here!

51:31.088 --> 51:33.264
Fjoölnir wants you close.

51:33.307 --> 51:36.005
If you lose me, will you come
and look for me, too?

51:37.181 --> 51:38.269
Will you?

51:38.312 --> 51:40.140
-Come here.

51:40.184 --> 51:42.186
♪

52:21.225 --> 52:23.183
♪

52:42.681 --> 52:44.726
♪

53:32.905 --> 53:36.169
Sit, Amleth, son of Aurvandil.

53:38.084 --> 53:40.652
Did our hen-eating friend
tell you of me?

53:42.523 --> 53:44.351
No.

53:46.571 --> 53:49.138
One much more talkative.

53:52.881 --> 53:54.753
An old fool.

53:57.016 --> 53:58.235
Poor Heimir.

53:59.845 --> 54:03.457
He speaks of days past

54:03.501 --> 54:05.764
and days yet to come.

54:08.810 --> 54:12.379
Fjoölnir cut out his tongue,

54:12.423 --> 54:16.601
plucked out his eyes
before killing him...

54:19.081 --> 54:22.215
...but I made him ones anew.

54:24.696 --> 54:27.089
Kind friend.

54:27.133 --> 54:29.657
Know that
I will avenge you, too.

54:29.701 --> 54:32.486
I fear you must address me.

54:32.530 --> 54:36.577
Alas, I made him no new ears.

54:38.100 --> 54:39.928
They also met
with Fjoölnir's blade.

54:39.972 --> 54:41.321
Enough!

54:41.365 --> 54:42.931
You know why I have come.

54:42.975 --> 54:46.761
You are still a beast
cloaked in man-flesh.

54:46.805 --> 54:48.676
Speak, witch.

54:48.720 --> 54:50.591
So be it, slave!

55:10.089 --> 55:12.874
Wandering prophet...

55:18.445 --> 55:20.447
...wake now...

55:22.101 --> 55:23.668
...from your murder.

55:43.252 --> 55:45.342
Hear me!

55:45.385 --> 55:48.649
Heimir is come!

55:53.350 --> 55:57.136
Hello, puppy.

55:57.179 --> 56:01.662
I seek the weapon the Norns
of Fate chose for my revenge.

56:01.706 --> 56:04.970
Hear me.

56:05.013 --> 56:08.713
Forged by the deadliest
war-smiths

56:08.756 --> 56:14.327
ever to crawl from under
the great worm's belly.

56:14.371 --> 56:20.768
A sword of
the most secretive rare iron,

56:20.812 --> 56:24.381
bound with bone of the joötnar.

56:24.424 --> 56:26.948
Weightless in its owner's hand,

56:26.992 --> 56:29.821
yet like a dragon's fang,

56:29.864 --> 56:31.823
its bite can never be dulled,

56:31.866 --> 56:34.608
-never broken nor bent.

56:34.652 --> 56:38.395
Its blade could only be quenched
in human blood.

56:40.745 --> 56:44.313
-It is a battle flame like
none other. -

56:45.314 --> 56:47.099
Its name:

56:47.142 --> 56:48.579
Draugr.

56:49.754 --> 56:51.843
The Undead.

56:56.021 --> 56:57.675
It is fated.

56:57.718 --> 56:59.459
Draugr!

57:11.471 --> 57:16.476
Yet,
difficult is the sword's nature,

57:16.520 --> 57:21.133
for it can only be unsheathed
in the dark of night

57:21.176 --> 57:23.962
or else at Hel's black gates.

57:24.005 --> 57:25.920
The Gates of Hel.

57:25.964 --> 57:28.619
There will my sword be just.

57:28.662 --> 57:32.579
I will enjoy feeding Draugr
till then in everlasting night.

57:32.623 --> 57:36.148
Then shall you also enjoy
the moment when you must choose

57:36.191 --> 57:41.327
between kindness for your kin
or hate for your enemies.

57:41.370 --> 57:43.677
That is nothing.

57:43.721 --> 57:45.940
My heart knows only revenge.

57:48.290 --> 57:49.857
Show it to me.

57:49.901 --> 57:53.818
You must make a visitation
to Draugr's owner,

57:53.861 --> 57:55.384
the mound dweller.

57:55.428 --> 57:57.474
♪

58:02.566 --> 58:05.220
Mark well the full moon's light.

58:06.787 --> 58:10.487
For shadows are not
hospitable hosts.

58:41.213 --> 58:43.258
♪

59:07.718 --> 59:09.763
♪

1:00:55.129 --> 1:00:58.350
Mark well the full moon's light!

1:02:04.590 --> 1:02:06.635
♪

1:02:34.185 --> 1:02:37.754
FJOÖ- Thórir will choose
our strongest.

1:02:37.797 --> 1:02:40.234
Tomorrow we'll prove
that Hákon Iron-Beard's men

1:02:40.278 --> 1:02:42.846
are born of mud and water.

1:02:44.761 --> 1:02:46.937
HALLGRIÍ- Mud will be
all that remains of them.

1:02:48.939 --> 1:02:50.418
FJOÖ-
Rakki!

1:03:03.780 --> 1:03:05.172
Rakki.

1:03:09.873 --> 1:03:11.918
♪

1:03:16.749 --> 1:03:18.359
Rakki.

1:03:18.403 --> 1:03:20.884
Take Rakki home.

1:03:20.927 --> 1:03:22.624
-And, you two...
-HALLGRIÍ- Rakki, come.

1:03:22.668 --> 1:03:24.626
...it's nearly dawn.
Get you to bed.

1:03:24.670 --> 1:03:25.758
HALLGRIÍ-
Yes, my lord.

1:03:25.802 --> 1:03:27.542
-Rakki.

1:03:37.552 --> 1:03:38.945
Wake, you.

1:03:39.990 --> 1:03:42.383
Fetch her. You know the one.

1:03:42.427 --> 1:03:43.776
Aye.

1:03:45.256 --> 1:03:47.258
Wake up, Olga. Wake up.

1:03:47.301 --> 1:03:48.825
Get to your feet.

1:03:56.702 --> 1:03:58.835
The hair of a Valkyrja...

1:04:00.227 --> 1:04:02.142
...on a savage Slav bitch.

1:04:08.148 --> 1:04:09.802
A little blood.

1:04:12.500 --> 1:04:14.198
Unclean whore!

1:04:19.159 --> 1:04:23.250
You will correct her, or you'll
both be dead in the ground.

1:04:34.174 --> 1:04:36.220
♪

1:04:40.354 --> 1:04:42.226
Thank the Norns
that the woman's tide

1:04:42.269 --> 1:04:46.708
is the only blood that runs
in your house tonight, coward.

1:04:49.973 --> 1:04:52.453
I am a fool.

1:04:52.497 --> 1:04:54.891
It was foretold that I would
slay my father's killer

1:04:54.934 --> 1:04:57.589
in a burning lake.

1:04:57.632 --> 1:04:59.721
Till that day comes,

1:04:59.765 --> 1:05:02.681
I will torment the man
who made my life a hell.

1:05:05.771 --> 1:05:07.773
Now sleep well, night blade.

1:05:08.992 --> 1:05:13.474
Yes, we thirst for vengeance,

1:05:13.518 --> 1:05:15.824
but we cannot escape our fate.

1:05:15.868 --> 1:05:17.914
♪

1:05:27.662 --> 1:05:29.403
MAN
Get them in line!

1:05:29.447 --> 1:05:30.970
-Look lively!

1:05:34.974 --> 1:05:37.411
-Move it!
-Don't be idle!

1:05:37.455 --> 1:05:39.152
Those are for the feast...

1:05:40.545 --> 1:05:42.503
Where are they taking us?

1:05:42.547 --> 1:05:44.766
Something about
the chieftain's feast.

1:05:45.898 --> 1:05:48.988
Last night, I saw him with you.

1:05:53.732 --> 1:05:55.995
Then you know Fjoölnir's touch
will not linger on me

1:05:56.039 --> 1:05:57.866
when I leave this island.

1:05:57.910 --> 1:06:00.173
You marked him well.

1:06:00.217 --> 1:06:03.307
And I have found the cold iron
that will strike him down.

1:06:06.658 --> 1:06:09.661
-When will you do it?
-When I must.

1:06:09.704 --> 1:06:11.315
For now, I will haunt this farm

1:06:11.358 --> 1:06:14.622
like a hungry corpse
returned from the grave.

1:06:14.666 --> 1:06:17.234
Fjoölnir thinks
Amleth is long dead.

1:06:17.277 --> 1:06:20.628
Yes, but what of your mother?

1:06:20.672 --> 1:06:23.631
She will revel
in Fjoölnir's anguish.

1:06:23.675 --> 1:06:26.547
She only feigns her love
to protect their child.

1:06:26.591 --> 1:06:28.462
-Won't she wish...
-When I free her,

1:06:28.506 --> 1:06:30.551
I will bring the boy if I must.

1:06:31.596 --> 1:06:33.250
They've moved me
back into the kitchen.

1:06:33.293 --> 1:06:34.381
-- Bjoörnulfr!
-If we can keep his men...

1:06:34.425 --> 1:06:36.122
Our plan will have to wait. Go.

1:06:36.166 --> 1:06:38.211
Bjoörnulfr, move!

1:06:44.652 --> 1:06:45.871
-You, to the back!
-- Move!

1:06:45.914 --> 1:06:47.655
Woman!

1:06:51.920 --> 1:06:54.053
- Thórir, my Lord,
we're lacking one man.

1:06:59.189 --> 1:07:01.800
I'm not a child.
My hair is my own.

1:07:01.843 --> 1:07:05.282
I know grown men who need
a woman to tend their hair.

1:07:06.718 --> 1:07:08.328
Get them in line.

1:07:08.372 --> 1:07:11.027
- You can celebrate
after the games, slave.

1:07:11.070 --> 1:07:12.593
Look lively!

1:07:14.204 --> 1:07:16.336
My lord.

1:07:16.380 --> 1:07:17.903
Come on!

1:07:17.946 --> 1:07:19.731
Thórir, my lord.

1:07:25.998 --> 1:07:28.044
Can you fight, slave?

1:07:29.784 --> 1:07:31.873
Look me in the eye, slave.

1:07:33.049 --> 1:07:35.486
I asked you
do you know how to fight.

1:07:38.097 --> 1:07:40.099
♪

1:08:01.033 --> 1:08:02.426
What are those?

1:08:03.644 --> 1:08:05.907
You've never seen
a knatttré before?

1:08:09.302 --> 1:08:11.565
By nightfall, you'll have
seen enough of them.

1:08:30.323 --> 1:08:31.977
Play for blood!

1:09:49.533 --> 1:09:52.057
You're shaming
our family's name!

1:09:52.100 --> 1:09:54.059
We need more men!

1:10:05.810 --> 1:10:07.507
Yeah!

1:10:09.683 --> 1:10:12.730
No! No!

1:10:42.325 --> 1:10:45.066
-Gunnar!
-No!

1:10:45.110 --> 1:10:47.460
Halt the game! Halt it now!

1:10:47.504 --> 1:10:49.157
-- Don't touch him!

1:10:49.201 --> 1:10:51.377
-FJOÖ- Gunnar!
-HAÁ- Halt the game!

1:10:51.421 --> 1:10:53.249
FJOÖ-
Gunnar! Gunnar!

1:10:53.292 --> 1:10:54.685
THOÓ-
Stupid runt!

1:10:54.728 --> 1:10:56.426
-GUDRUÚ- No!

1:11:15.923 --> 1:11:18.274
-GUDRUÚ- Gunnar. Gunnar.
-FJOÖ- Wake up. Wake up.

1:11:18.317 --> 1:11:20.145
Stupid, stupid boy. Wake up.

1:11:21.929 --> 1:11:24.323
-GUDRUÚ- Gunnar. Gunnar. Gunnar.
-FJOÖ- Gunnar.

1:11:24.367 --> 1:11:25.542
-Wake up, come on.

1:11:25.585 --> 1:11:28.196
Wake up, Gunnar. Wake up!

1:11:28.240 --> 1:11:30.242
GUDRUÚN
Gunnar. Gunnar. Gunnar.

1:11:30.286 --> 1:11:32.070
-FJOÖ- Wake up.
-Gunnar. Gunnar.

1:11:32.113 --> 1:11:33.376
-Wake up!
-No.

1:11:36.553 --> 1:11:38.337
Wake up.

1:11:42.080 --> 1:11:43.429
Did we win?

1:11:45.562 --> 1:11:48.869
Spoken like
a true chieftain's son.

1:11:50.828 --> 1:11:52.046
A brave boy.

1:11:52.090 --> 1:11:53.744
A brave young man.

1:13:01.551 --> 1:13:02.900
You.

1:13:06.991 --> 1:13:08.166
This way.

1:13:18.394 --> 1:13:20.744
You showed yourself brave

1:13:20.787 --> 1:13:22.136
and loyal.

1:13:23.181 --> 1:13:24.574
When we return to the farm,

1:13:24.617 --> 1:13:27.446
certain privileges
will be granted you.

1:13:27.490 --> 1:13:29.753
Your work will be
less burdensome.

1:13:29.796 --> 1:13:32.495
You will command others' burden.

1:13:32.538 --> 1:13:36.324
And, Bjoörnulfr,

1:13:36.368 --> 1:13:38.196
as a reward
for winning us the game,

1:13:38.239 --> 1:13:40.372
I'll let you choose a woman
for yourself.

1:13:40.416 --> 1:13:44.202
Even that Slav bitch
I've seen you eyeing.

1:13:44.245 --> 1:13:46.117
Father found her too...

1:13:47.379 --> 1:13:48.511
...unyielding.

1:13:57.955 --> 1:14:01.001
But know that we will never
make you a free man.

1:14:02.481 --> 1:14:06.616
The stench of a lowborn slave
cannot escape him.

1:14:08.444 --> 1:14:09.662
Yes.

1:14:10.924 --> 1:14:12.970
Thank you.

1:14:17.061 --> 1:14:20.020
- We'll miss you
cleaning the shithouse.

1:14:29.726 --> 1:14:32.816
♪

1:15:00.017 --> 1:15:01.932
Olga.

1:15:11.724 --> 1:15:13.334
You found me.

1:15:16.599 --> 1:15:18.209
Were you lost?

1:15:20.385 --> 1:15:22.605
Only if you were searching
for me.

1:15:55.028 --> 1:15:56.552
What do you do?

1:15:59.816 --> 1:16:04.603
Here, where the threads of fate
have bound us together,

1:16:04.647 --> 1:16:09.086
embraced beneath the trees,
here I speak with the earth.

1:16:10.304 --> 1:16:11.958
What does she tell you?

1:16:19.052 --> 1:16:21.533
How to reach your mother.

1:16:22.795 --> 1:16:26.712
My Earth magic will stoke
the flames of your sword.

1:16:40.683 --> 1:16:42.772
Tomorrow night, you and I...

1:16:44.687 --> 1:16:48.125
...will begin this nightmare

1:16:48.168 --> 1:16:51.607
and bring Fjoölnir's life
to chaos.

1:16:59.876 --> 1:17:01.921
-Finish.

1:17:05.446 --> 1:17:07.187
Back to the stalls.

1:17:10.190 --> 1:17:12.671
Hey, hey.

1:17:12.715 --> 1:17:14.847
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

1:17:16.762 --> 1:17:18.503
You.

1:17:19.460 --> 1:17:20.853
♪

1:17:34.127 --> 1:17:36.956
The servants of Freyr.

1:17:37.000 --> 1:17:38.915
Lay them before our lord's feet.

1:18:22.872 --> 1:18:24.917
-- You weakling.

1:18:39.323 --> 1:18:40.846
-- Fear not.

1:18:40.890 --> 1:18:42.282
-You're the first of many.
-- No.

1:18:42.326 --> 1:18:43.719
Please! We'll set you free!

1:18:49.202 --> 1:18:52.118
Oh, I will find who did this.

1:18:52.162 --> 1:18:56.514
I will find them,
and I will tear out their eyes!

1:18:56.557 --> 1:18:59.473
And I will
tear out their tongues!

1:18:59.517 --> 1:19:03.695
They will all sup in Hel!

1:19:05.131 --> 1:19:06.654
Look, Father.

1:19:06.698 --> 1:19:09.048
Look what has been done
to my brave friends.

1:19:10.484 --> 1:19:12.138
Christian monsters!

1:19:12.182 --> 1:19:13.792
Monsters!

1:19:14.837 --> 1:19:16.273
Monsters!

1:19:16.316 --> 1:19:18.884
-Lack-beard, did you do this?!

1:19:18.928 --> 1:19:21.887
Answer me! Answer me!

1:19:21.931 --> 1:19:23.671
-Stop this!

1:19:23.715 --> 1:19:25.761
-Son.

1:19:26.892 --> 1:19:29.112
Regain your calm.

1:19:34.030 --> 1:19:35.988
They were good boys.

1:19:37.468 --> 1:19:41.124
By Freyr, we will avenge them.

1:19:43.169 --> 1:19:44.823
Take him away.

1:19:47.957 --> 1:19:49.915
Is Thórir right?

1:19:49.959 --> 1:19:52.483
Could it be
the Christian swines?

1:19:54.006 --> 1:19:58.054
Their god is a corpse
nailed to a tree.

1:19:58.097 --> 1:19:59.707
For what?

1:20:01.405 --> 1:20:03.668
These boys never touched them.

1:20:03.711 --> 1:20:06.323
And how might they find weapons?

1:20:10.153 --> 1:20:12.198
♪

1:20:26.299 --> 1:20:28.084
No.

1:20:28.127 --> 1:20:31.609
These wounds
are not of our world.

1:20:37.310 --> 1:20:42.315
This distempered spirit
will ride again.

1:20:42.359 --> 1:20:44.883
It wields a hungry blade.

1:20:46.929 --> 1:20:48.060
Go.

1:20:48.104 --> 1:20:50.367
I will prepare a sacrifice.

1:20:54.066 --> 1:20:56.286
On with you!

1:20:56.329 --> 1:20:58.810
-Blood-drinking Christians!

1:20:59.898 --> 1:21:02.074
Do as you're told.

1:21:03.467 --> 1:21:05.034
Go.

1:21:07.210 --> 1:21:09.473
The mushrooms, I have them.

1:21:09.516 --> 1:21:10.996
Not tonight.

1:21:11.040 --> 1:21:13.433
The spirits will ride
and spill more blood.

1:21:13.477 --> 1:21:15.522
♪

1:21:28.231 --> 1:21:30.276
♪

1:21:43.986 --> 1:21:48.729
Black she-spirit, abate.

1:21:48.773 --> 1:21:52.081
Bear this offering
to your mistress

1:21:52.124 --> 1:21:55.214
and sheath
your rageful corpse-hound.

1:22:14.364 --> 1:22:16.148
-FJOÖ- Rakki.
-GUDRUÚ- Rakki!

1:22:16.192 --> 1:22:17.367
FJOÖ-
What is it, Rakki?

1:22:17.410 --> 1:22:19.064
GUDRUÚ-
Rakki!

1:22:19.108 --> 1:22:20.544
Down, Rakki!

1:22:20.587 --> 1:22:22.372
-Rakki! Ra...

1:22:27.159 --> 1:22:29.945
-GUDRUÚ- Rakki! Rakki!

1:22:48.398 --> 1:22:50.443
♪

1:23:09.332 --> 1:23:11.073
Free her.

1:23:21.083 --> 1:23:24.216
Freyr, it seems,
has chosen for himself

1:23:24.260 --> 1:23:26.958
who is deemed fit for sacrifice.

1:23:27.002 --> 1:23:29.221
AÁ-
Blighted by his blood...

1:23:29.265 --> 1:23:31.919
Let us hope
his hunger has been sated.

1:23:31.963 --> 1:23:34.052
This is not the work of my god.

1:23:36.750 --> 1:23:39.188
This is trollish sorcery.

1:23:41.407 --> 1:23:46.195
FJOÖ- Tonight, you will be
armed to defend the farm,

1:23:46.238 --> 1:23:49.198
-for this is also your home.

1:23:49.241 --> 1:23:51.548
THOÓ- How can we trust them
to protect us?

1:23:51.591 --> 1:23:52.897
HALLGRIÍ-
Here, dog.

1:23:52.940 --> 1:23:54.377
Your father
does not want an uprising

1:23:54.420 --> 1:23:55.856
-by emboldened slaves.
-HALLGRIÍ- Go!

1:23:55.900 --> 1:23:57.945
Do not doubt his wisdom.

1:23:57.989 --> 1:23:59.730
HALLGRIÍ-
Walk!

1:24:05.431 --> 1:24:07.477
♪

1:24:17.748 --> 1:24:20.881
Black dreams arise.

1:24:22.231 --> 1:24:26.583
Hey, slaves, I like your sticks!

1:24:28.933 --> 1:24:33.024
Yeah, good luck fending off
the demon with that thing.

1:24:36.636 --> 1:24:37.942
Here.

1:24:51.390 --> 1:24:52.696
Hungry?

1:24:55.655 --> 1:24:58.484
Tonight, you are the food!

1:25:03.663 --> 1:25:05.709
♪

1:25:14.196 --> 1:25:16.372
Go take some night air.

1:25:16.415 --> 1:25:18.113
I'll finish here.

1:25:19.723 --> 1:25:21.116
Go on.

1:25:31.952 --> 1:25:35.086
♪

1:26:22.786 --> 1:26:24.788
-- Get them away!
-- Run!

1:26:24.831 --> 1:26:26.572
-She's a she-devil!

1:26:42.022 --> 1:26:43.720
FJOÖ-
Touch them not.

1:26:43.763 --> 1:26:46.201
Look not into their eyes.

1:26:46.244 --> 1:26:48.594
The night spirits
have entered their skins

1:26:48.638 --> 1:26:50.727
and are riding their minds.

1:26:53.860 --> 1:26:56.298
Thórir! Out, Dísir!

1:26:56.341 --> 1:26:58.996
-Begone!

1:27:01.607 --> 1:27:03.566
We will meet you before dawn.

1:27:23.020 --> 1:27:25.065
♪

1:27:41.604 --> 1:27:43.649
♪

1:27:57.010 --> 1:27:58.403
Father.

1:28:08.065 --> 1:28:09.458
Leave me.

1:28:48.323 --> 1:28:50.107
Your sword is long.

1:28:50.150 --> 1:28:51.804
Stop your jest.

1:28:58.028 --> 1:28:59.856
I am your son.

1:29:03.338 --> 1:29:04.687
Amleth?

1:29:10.432 --> 1:29:13.957
You live still?

1:29:14.000 --> 1:29:15.611
A life of death.

1:29:17.874 --> 1:29:20.442
Yet I swore to survive
till this moment.

1:29:21.878 --> 1:29:24.359
Tomorrow, I shall finish
my deeds in honor.

1:29:26.056 --> 1:29:29.320
Only then will I discover
whether living is to my liking.

1:29:29.364 --> 1:29:32.192
You are your mother's son.

1:29:32.236 --> 1:29:34.499
And my father's.

1:29:34.543 --> 1:29:37.763
I am come to avenge
King Aurvandil,

1:29:37.807 --> 1:29:40.723
to choke my traitorous uncle
in his death-blood...

1:29:42.464 --> 1:29:44.291
...and to free you.

1:29:47.033 --> 1:29:50.385
I see you have inherited
your father's simpleness.

1:29:52.909 --> 1:29:54.301
What say you?

1:29:54.345 --> 1:29:56.869
I never mourned him.

1:29:56.913 --> 1:29:58.523
You were his queen.

1:30:01.396 --> 1:30:04.964
Your father endured me...

1:30:06.313 --> 1:30:08.403
...because I bore him a son.

1:30:10.230 --> 1:30:12.276
-N-No.
-His affections were

1:30:12.319 --> 1:30:15.322
only for silver
and rutting his whores.

1:30:15.366 --> 1:30:17.847
I know not if he had
heart enough to love you.

1:30:17.890 --> 1:30:19.283
S... Silence.

1:30:19.326 --> 1:30:21.198
He was a coward
feigning to be a king.

1:30:21.241 --> 1:30:22.765
He was nothing.

1:30:22.808 --> 1:30:25.507
He was just another proud,
lust-stained slaver.

1:30:25.550 --> 1:30:27.509
Hold your tongue!

1:30:29.424 --> 1:30:31.338
You spit in the face
of your dead husband.

1:30:31.382 --> 1:30:32.818
Yet his brother...

1:30:34.298 --> 1:30:37.170
...his fine brother.

1:30:40.043 --> 1:30:44.482
A bastard has no shame
of himself nor his trade.

1:30:44.526 --> 1:30:47.964
Your uncle loved me,
though he knew well my past.

1:30:53.012 --> 1:30:54.579
Amleth.

1:30:56.363 --> 1:31:00.367
Even now, you believe the
fairy tale I told you is true?

1:31:00.411 --> 1:31:04.546
"A noble bride hailing from
the land of Brittany"?

1:31:06.025 --> 1:31:09.594
I never began as his bride.

1:31:13.206 --> 1:31:15.687
How easily we all become
princesses again

1:31:15.731 --> 1:31:19.386
when the beasts
take us for their wives.

1:31:22.694 --> 1:31:24.391
Yes.

1:31:24.435 --> 1:31:26.872
You were forced
upon your mother.

1:31:26.916 --> 1:31:30.702
Gunnar was received freely
with love.

1:31:30.746 --> 1:31:32.356
No.

1:31:34.314 --> 1:31:36.012
And know you this:

1:31:36.055 --> 1:31:40.495
It was I who begged on my knees

1:31:40.538 --> 1:31:43.541
for Fjoölnir
to kill King Aurvandil.

1:31:43.585 --> 1:31:46.283
I pressed my lips

1:31:46.326 --> 1:31:50.679
upon his strong, sweet hand.

1:31:50.722 --> 1:31:55.553
I kissed it and I begged.

1:31:58.121 --> 1:32:01.254
And so this day
would never come,

1:32:01.298 --> 1:32:03.256
Fjoölnir ordered your death,

1:32:03.300 --> 1:32:06.346
along with
your own mother's blessing.

1:32:09.872 --> 1:32:11.438
But I saw it.

1:32:13.397 --> 1:32:17.749
I saw Fjoölnir
carrying you away... screaming.

1:32:17.793 --> 1:32:20.099
Screaming?

1:32:20.143 --> 1:32:22.014
I was laughing.

1:32:22.058 --> 1:32:23.799
Lies!

1:32:25.931 --> 1:32:29.021
Now that you are here,
what do we do?

1:32:29.065 --> 1:32:32.329
I should kill you
and all that is dear to you.

1:32:32.372 --> 1:32:34.157
But you love me.

1:32:34.200 --> 1:32:38.770
A son loves his mother
and a mother loves her son.

1:32:41.077 --> 1:32:43.383
And you saved
your brother's life.

1:32:43.427 --> 1:32:45.777
You.

1:32:45.821 --> 1:32:48.998
You love.

1:32:51.043 --> 1:32:53.611
You...

1:32:53.655 --> 1:32:55.221
love.

1:32:57.876 --> 1:33:00.139
None but me knows who you are.

1:33:01.619 --> 1:33:05.101
And you are so hot for revenge,

1:33:05.144 --> 1:33:08.495
child born of savagery.

1:33:09.801 --> 1:33:12.064
-If you kill Fjoölnir...

1:33:12.108 --> 1:33:15.720
if you kill Thórir,

1:33:15.764 --> 1:33:20.638
and if you are so untamed
as to kill my Gunnar...

1:33:24.294 --> 1:33:27.863
...you would be
my new king, Amleth,

1:33:27.906 --> 1:33:30.605
and together...

1:33:30.648 --> 1:33:32.781
we will rule.

1:33:32.824 --> 1:33:34.870
♪

1:33:43.748 --> 1:33:46.185
-Bitch!
-Your taste and your mind

1:33:46.229 --> 1:33:48.753
reek of your foul father!

1:33:48.797 --> 1:33:50.189
You should have joined him
in death!

1:33:50.233 --> 1:33:52.017
Your words are poison!

1:33:52.061 --> 1:33:54.846
I am your death!

1:34:09.731 --> 1:34:10.862
Die!

1:34:31.448 --> 1:34:33.929
-Where is your mother?

1:34:33.972 --> 1:34:36.192
Tell me.

1:34:36.235 --> 1:34:37.497
Where?

1:34:38.673 --> 1:34:41.327
She's as evil as Fjoölnir.

1:34:41.371 --> 1:34:45.070
I will destroy him
and all that she loved.

1:34:45.114 --> 1:34:48.639
-I will become a hailstorm
of iron and steel! -

1:34:48.683 --> 1:34:51.555
I will have my vengeance!

1:34:51.598 --> 1:34:53.992
And more.

1:34:54.036 --> 1:34:56.386
Then what must we do now?

1:34:59.258 --> 1:35:01.130
I... I...

1:35:01.173 --> 1:35:03.741
I must take to the hills.

1:35:03.785 --> 1:35:06.570
My mother discovered who I am.
Soon everyone will.

1:35:06.613 --> 1:35:09.529
-I'll go with you.
-No.

1:35:09.573 --> 1:35:11.531
They cannot know
you are part of this.

1:35:11.575 --> 1:35:13.533
Come morning,
they will hunt for me.

1:35:13.577 --> 1:35:15.013
Why?

1:35:18.800 --> 1:35:21.019
You killed her?

1:35:21.063 --> 1:35:23.282
I would not kill a woman.

1:35:23.326 --> 1:35:25.545
Not even her.

1:35:25.589 --> 1:35:28.505
Thórir met his end by my fury.

1:35:28.548 --> 1:35:30.202
Well, good riddance.

1:35:31.638 --> 1:35:35.207
Tomorrow night, you will return
and kill Fjoölnir?

1:35:35.251 --> 1:35:38.080
If the Norns of Fate allow it.

1:35:38.123 --> 1:35:41.213
And whatever happens tomorrow,
be ready to run.

1:35:41.257 --> 1:35:43.302
♪

1:35:49.178 --> 1:35:51.180
♪

1:36:23.386 --> 1:36:25.388
His heart.

1:36:25.431 --> 1:36:26.519
His...

1:36:27.738 --> 1:36:30.785
His heart.
It's taken his heart!

1:36:34.614 --> 1:36:36.834
What evil is this?!

1:36:38.880 --> 1:36:44.886
What evil eats the hearts
of brave young men?!

1:36:46.365 --> 1:36:49.716
Freyr, do you hear me?!

1:36:49.760 --> 1:36:51.327
Behave.

1:36:51.370 --> 1:36:54.243
-Be a man in front of
your inferiors. -

1:36:54.286 --> 1:36:57.637
There is no evil spirit here.

1:36:57.681 --> 1:37:01.076
I told you. I told you.

1:37:01.119 --> 1:37:04.601
It is my cursed son Amleth.

1:37:04.644 --> 1:37:07.299
We rid ourselves of him
as a boy.

1:37:07.343 --> 1:37:09.301
You must believe me.

1:37:09.345 --> 1:37:11.129
He is here.

1:37:11.173 --> 1:37:13.697
The progeny of Aurvandil
lives still.

1:37:13.740 --> 1:37:17.962
I fear he was led here
by the raven-spirit

1:37:18.006 --> 1:37:19.616
of your dead brother.

1:37:19.659 --> 1:37:21.923
-It's not possible.
-Think.

1:37:21.966 --> 1:37:23.315
He's killed your men.

1:37:23.359 --> 1:37:26.710
He has murdered your eldest son.

1:37:26.753 --> 1:37:29.713
And he will not rest
till you lie cold in the ground

1:37:29.756 --> 1:37:33.238
and our own Gunnar
lies slain beside you.

1:37:33.282 --> 1:37:35.632
It is Amleth.

1:37:38.200 --> 1:37:41.333
No god can help you
with this task.

1:37:41.377 --> 1:37:43.031
You must discover my son

1:37:43.074 --> 1:37:46.599
and kill him
with your own hands.

1:37:46.643 --> 1:37:51.213
Let my words be the whetstone
to your biting rage,

1:37:51.256 --> 1:37:54.912
for the mischief of last night
was not the work of one man.

1:37:54.956 --> 1:37:58.307
Find the slaves
who ally with him.

1:37:59.743 --> 1:38:01.310
Find them!

1:38:03.268 --> 1:38:04.748
On your knees!

1:38:04.791 --> 1:38:07.098
-HALLGRIÍ- Down with you!

1:38:07.142 --> 1:38:08.883
Down with the lot of you!

1:38:16.978 --> 1:38:20.111
I know not, nor care not,

1:38:20.155 --> 1:38:23.027
if that slave aided
in the death of my son...

1:38:24.724 --> 1:38:26.509
...but this is the end
you will all meet

1:38:26.552 --> 1:38:29.599
if you speak not what you know.

1:38:31.253 --> 1:38:32.384
No?

1:38:39.348 --> 1:38:42.568
I see you're no longer afraid
of a woman's blood.

1:38:42.612 --> 1:38:43.961
You.

1:38:44.005 --> 1:38:46.311
-Of course it is you.

1:38:46.355 --> 1:38:48.270
Fjoölnir!

1:38:48.313 --> 1:38:49.967
Let her alone!

1:38:50.011 --> 1:38:53.928
I offer you your son's heart
in exchange for her life!

1:38:54.929 --> 1:38:57.627
♪

1:39:02.066 --> 1:39:04.721
I am Amleth the Bear-Wolf,

1:39:04.764 --> 1:39:08.159
son of
King Aurvandil War-Raven,

1:39:08.203 --> 1:39:12.163
and I am his vengeance!

1:39:12.207 --> 1:39:14.600
-Kill him!

1:39:14.644 --> 1:39:16.167
FJOÖ-
Bring him to me!

1:39:16.211 --> 1:39:19.257
-GUDRUÚ- Kill him!
-He's mine!

1:40:39.424 --> 1:40:40.947
In the end...

1:40:42.471 --> 1:40:45.039
...you're just like your father.

1:40:46.953 --> 1:40:50.087
Evil begets evil.

1:40:54.135 --> 1:40:57.225
How do you know
it's your son's heart...

1:40:58.835 --> 1:41:02.273
...and not the heart of a rabid
dog killed two nights ago?

1:41:07.583 --> 1:41:10.368
-FJOÖ- Where is it?!

1:41:15.634 --> 1:41:17.549
You cannot kill me.

1:41:19.073 --> 1:41:22.424
Even if you were
to strike me with your sword,

1:41:22.467 --> 1:41:24.339
it would not bite.

1:41:26.123 --> 1:41:28.038
It is not my time.

1:41:28.082 --> 1:41:31.172
I will die in battle.

1:41:32.260 --> 1:41:34.827
Where is my son's heart?!

1:41:40.877 --> 1:41:43.706
OÓdinn the All-Father

1:41:43.749 --> 1:41:46.448
will vanquish
your god of erections.

1:41:47.666 --> 1:41:48.841
Fear him.

1:41:48.885 --> 1:41:50.321
Silence!

1:41:52.062 --> 1:41:55.152
I will come back for your heart.

1:41:55.196 --> 1:41:58.677
And your mother and I
will eat it.

1:42:29.230 --> 1:42:31.232
♪

1:43:00.609 --> 1:43:02.654
♪

1:43:08.617 --> 1:43:12.969
OÓdinn, let the Valkyrja,
your warrior maiden,

1:43:13.012 --> 1:43:17.278
fly me to your shining gates.

1:43:25.677 --> 1:43:28.593
I see my father and mother.

1:43:31.901 --> 1:43:33.990
I see my dead kindred.

1:43:38.255 --> 1:43:41.867
I see my master
in Freyja's hall.

1:43:41.911 --> 1:43:43.956
He calls me to him.

1:44:57.116 --> 1:45:00.337
Tonight, our mourning
for Thórir ends.

1:45:15.439 --> 1:45:19.356
May the neck-ale
of this swift steed

1:45:19.400 --> 1:45:24.448
hasten you to the highest tree
of the battle-weavers, brother.

1:45:37.374 --> 1:45:39.376
♪

1:45:59.918 --> 1:46:03.835
My hour of grief

1:46:03.879 --> 1:46:05.620
has passed.

1:46:06.969 --> 1:46:12.017
The time of
wrath-kindled revenge

1:46:12.061 --> 1:46:14.411
is upon us!

1:46:44.136 --> 1:46:46.182
♪

1:46:58.281 --> 1:47:00.326
♪

1:47:55.643 --> 1:47:57.688
♪

1:48:00.474 --> 1:48:02.780
This is not Valhoöll?

1:48:02.824 --> 1:48:04.956
I did not carry you that far.

1:48:08.743 --> 1:48:11.049
I am no Valkyrja.

1:48:11.093 --> 1:48:14.183
The dreams of your afterlife
must wait.

1:48:15.750 --> 1:48:17.621
Besides...

1:48:17.665 --> 1:48:19.493
I'm not done with you yet.

1:48:19.536 --> 1:48:21.538
♪

1:48:39.469 --> 1:48:40.992
My fate brought me to Iceland

1:48:41.036 --> 1:48:43.299
to carry out
my pledge of vengeance.

1:48:45.780 --> 1:48:47.346
But my fate...

1:48:49.740 --> 1:48:52.177
...did not ready me
for finding you.

1:48:54.702 --> 1:48:58.706
I thought I must always
shield my heart in stone.

1:48:58.749 --> 1:49:01.665
I could not think
I would open it to a Northman.

1:49:04.538 --> 1:49:07.236
You sacrificed yourself
that I could flee.

1:49:08.454 --> 1:49:10.500
And you came back for me.

1:49:19.422 --> 1:49:22.468
I have never f-felt close
to another person.

1:49:25.776 --> 1:49:27.648
Not since I was a child.

1:49:29.519 --> 1:49:31.565
I curse your mother's evil.

1:49:34.655 --> 1:49:36.657
She murdered my past.

1:49:38.223 --> 1:49:40.399
Could it not be
that your Norns of Fate

1:49:40.443 --> 1:49:42.924
have spun another thread
for you to follow?

1:49:46.275 --> 1:49:48.277
What do your earth gods
tell you?

1:49:50.540 --> 1:49:53.325
That wherever I go,
I must take you with me.

1:49:54.805 --> 1:49:56.851
♪

1:49:59.897 --> 1:50:02.900
I have kinsmen in Orkney.

1:50:02.944 --> 1:50:07.078
We could find s... we could
find safe passage there.

1:50:07.122 --> 1:50:08.602
Together.

1:50:11.692 --> 1:50:13.345
Yet I cannot truly believe

1:50:13.389 --> 1:50:16.174
that you have extinguished
your fire for vengeance.

1:50:19.525 --> 1:50:21.615
Hate is all I have ever known.

1:50:23.834 --> 1:50:26.489
But I wish
I could be free of it.

1:50:26.532 --> 1:50:28.709
That is for you to choose.

1:50:30.972 --> 1:50:33.235
Let us find our future.

1:50:38.588 --> 1:50:40.634
♪

1:51:03.178 --> 1:51:05.441
Welcome, seafarers.

1:51:05.484 --> 1:51:07.356
The deck of
this wooden saddle-beast

1:51:07.399 --> 1:51:10.446
will be the only ground
you tread for 21 days.

1:51:16.408 --> 1:51:20.021
I was expecting
more of Fjoölnir's men.

1:51:20.064 --> 1:51:22.371
His son was to join us.

1:51:31.075 --> 1:51:33.121
♪

1:51:34.818 --> 1:51:36.515
Anchor up!

1:51:36.559 --> 1:51:38.561
Sail down!

1:51:41.346 --> 1:51:42.913
Secure the shrouds.

1:51:42.957 --> 1:51:44.610
Shrouds secured.

1:51:46.787 --> 1:51:48.658
Keep her downwind, helmsman.

1:51:48.702 --> 1:51:50.094
Aye, aye!

1:51:51.617 --> 1:51:53.271
Your wound.

1:51:55.404 --> 1:51:58.581
It is nothing
to what we have endured.

1:51:58.624 --> 1:52:00.235
I have forgotten it already.

1:52:12.377 --> 1:52:14.423
♪

1:52:31.092 --> 1:52:32.963
My family's blood.

1:52:35.618 --> 1:52:37.620
My own blood is inside you.

1:52:39.840 --> 1:52:43.887
You are the well
our dynasty will spring from.

1:52:43.931 --> 1:52:45.671
I did not wish you to know

1:52:45.715 --> 1:52:49.153
until I could trust
that our child would be safe.

1:52:54.071 --> 1:52:57.074
While Fjoölnir lives,
our children will never be safe.

1:52:58.728 --> 1:53:00.686
If he but knew of this,

1:53:00.730 --> 1:53:03.298
he would hunt you
with all the fire of the gods.

1:53:04.342 --> 1:53:05.517
It cannot wait.

1:53:05.561 --> 1:53:07.084
Stop this.

1:53:07.128 --> 1:53:11.088
There is now a living thread
that binds us.

1:53:11.132 --> 1:53:13.003
I was a fool.

1:53:15.136 --> 1:53:17.616
I wished to flee with you
from my fate.

1:53:21.795 --> 1:53:23.797
♪

1:53:31.674 --> 1:53:34.111
My vision shows me
you will have two.

1:53:35.983 --> 1:53:38.550
And my sword will save them.

1:53:47.255 --> 1:53:49.431
But you must come with us.

1:53:49.474 --> 1:53:50.911
You must!

1:53:51.912 --> 1:53:55.263
It was prophesied
that I must choose...

1:53:55.306 --> 1:54:00.007
between kindness for my kin
and hate for my enemies.

1:54:00.050 --> 1:54:02.792
And see what hope
we have before us.

1:54:11.932 --> 1:54:13.847
I choose both.

1:54:21.767 --> 1:54:23.160
Take her to Orkney.

1:54:23.204 --> 1:54:25.423
In return for this ring,
my kinsmen will give you

1:54:25.467 --> 1:54:26.772
-ninefold its worth.
-No!

1:54:26.816 --> 1:54:28.296
No!

1:54:28.339 --> 1:54:29.471
Amleth!

1:54:33.431 --> 1:54:35.564
You will be mother to a king!

1:54:36.782 --> 1:54:38.306
We cannot escape our fate.

1:54:38.349 --> 1:54:40.090
No!

1:54:40.134 --> 1:54:42.440
Amleth!

1:54:49.795 --> 1:54:51.841
♪

1:55:20.957 --> 1:55:23.786
♪

1:56:04.870 --> 1:56:06.916
♪

1:56:24.151 --> 1:56:26.283
-- It's the slave!

1:56:28.938 --> 1:56:30.026
It's him!

1:56:35.292 --> 1:56:36.380
Close off the house!

1:56:52.962 --> 1:56:56.270
The cub you once hunted
ate of your nose.

1:56:56.313 --> 1:56:59.142
Now the wolf is grown.

1:56:59.186 --> 1:57:01.057
He hungers for the rest.

1:57:08.108 --> 1:57:11.850
Whatever you hear,
you must stay hidden.

1:57:14.940 --> 1:57:16.594
Keep him safe.

1:57:18.161 --> 1:57:20.120
Keep both of you safe.

1:57:20.163 --> 1:57:21.904
I will.

1:57:21.947 --> 1:57:23.993
♪

1:57:50.454 --> 1:57:53.196
Take your freedom...

1:57:53.240 --> 1:57:55.285
and do with it what you will.

1:57:56.634 --> 1:57:58.680
♪

1:58:06.905 --> 1:58:08.298
Fjoölnir!

1:58:21.137 --> 1:58:22.878
Never!

1:58:35.934 --> 1:58:37.980
In the heart.

1:58:41.157 --> 1:58:42.985
Thank you.

1:58:51.124 --> 1:58:53.213
-- Mother!

1:59:10.708 --> 1:59:12.754
♪

1:59:39.259 --> 1:59:41.261
♪

2:00:11.813 --> 2:00:15.164
I will meet you
at the Gates of Hel.

2:00:16.905 --> 2:00:19.473
At the Gates of Hel,

2:00:19.516 --> 2:00:21.214
you will find me.

2:00:22.432 --> 2:00:24.347
And there you will die...

2:00:25.783 --> 2:00:28.960
...by the hand
that killed your father.

2:00:32.529 --> 2:00:34.575
♪

2:00:49.459 --> 2:00:51.244
HALLDOÓ-
Let me down!

2:01:14.267 --> 2:01:16.269
♪

2:01:43.905 --> 2:01:45.950
♪

2:02:08.277 --> 2:02:10.323
♪

2:02:38.394 --> 2:02:41.179
Slain by iron,

2:02:41.223 --> 2:02:44.661
we shall all meet again in the
stronghold of the All-Father.

2:04:02.435 --> 2:04:04.872
My blood will live on!

2:04:04.915 --> 2:04:07.048
Valhoöll awaits!

2:04:19.756 --> 2:04:21.802
♪

2:06:20.616 --> 2:06:22.618
♪

2:07:01.526 --> 2:07:03.572
♪

2:07:39.739 --> 2:07:41.741
♪

2:07:45.135 --> 2:07:48.965
- The thread that binds us
can never break.

2:07:54.884 --> 2:07:56.581
We are safe.

2:08:04.764 --> 2:08:07.636
Now make your passage.

2:08:07.680 --> 2:08:09.682
♪

2:08:27.787 --> 2:08:29.832
♪

